nce with development of large, complex, safety-critical software systems. Experience across the software development life cycle (requirements, design, implementation, and test) and the entry and exit criteria associated with Program/Project milestone reviews. Familiarity with software architectures and systems & software engineering practices. Experience developing and/or evaluating FMEA, Hazard Analysis, and FTA products with emphasis on software components and integration in hardware systems. Experience with NASA, Government approved Industry, or DoD software assurance requirements, standards, manuals and handbooks, and assessing compliance with these products. Experience performing software safety and testing activities related to embedded software systems. Excellent verbal and written English language skills, good communication skills, and ability to interact well in group meeting/working environments with team members, development organizations and customers. Proficiency with MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook). Must be able to obtain and maintain a Public Trust Security Clearance Other Desired Skills: Experience with NASA flight programs involving Human related spacecraft / launch vehicle systems and domains such as rocket engine propulsion control; flight dynamics; vehicle system management; fault protection / fault management; launch, flight, and abort operations / processes; software safety; and mission assurance Familiarity with Mil-STD-882 Familiarity with DO-178 Avionics Software Standard Experience reviewing and/or developing Software Assurance Plans, Software Requirements Specifications, and Software Test Plans Knowledge of software testing and performing SQA audit Experience or knowledge of SEI Capability Maturity Model Integration (CMMI) implementations Experience with complex electronics (e.g. ASICs, FPGAs) and programmable logic devices Familiarity with Agile software development processes Experience with NASA-STD 8739.8 and NASA-STD 8719.13 and the identification of safety critical software requirements and analysis of related design concepts Required to be regular in attendance (per agreed to work hours schedule), consistently punctual and be relied upon to successfully complete all assignments. Bastion participates in the e-Verify and EEO ",
